        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 23 at 6:03PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Burro Flats, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mescalero, Cloudcroft, Sacramento, Mayhill, Silver Lake, Weed, Elk
Silver, Mountain Park, Upper Nogal Canyon, South Tularosa Canyon,
Head Springs, Sixteen Springs, Benson Ridge, Cox Canyon, Dry Canyon,
Karr Canyon, James Canyon, Hay Canyon, Soldier Canyon, and Upper Dry
Burnt Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
